WEBVTT

00:06.793 --> 00:09.724
[mellow music]

00:09.793 --> 00:17.000
♪ ♪

00:31.724 --> 00:33.275
- What time is it?

00:33.344 --> 00:35.827
- Almost 5:00.
- P.m.?

00:35.896 --> 00:37.689
- A.m.

00:38.931 --> 00:43.896
- Shit, I don't know whether
to eat breakfast or dinner.

00:43.965 --> 00:46.206
- It doesn't really matter.

00:46.275 --> 00:50.206
- Fuck it, I'll just get
a coffee and a muffin.

00:56.551 --> 00:57.827
What's that?

00:57.896 --> 01:00.137
- Sponsoring Alvarez's
green card.

01:00.206 --> 01:02.000
12 pages
of mind-numbing paperwork

01:02.068 --> 01:03.655
she's been up my ass for.

01:03.724 --> 01:06.793
- You better hope their native
language is chicken scratch.

01:06.862 --> 01:09.344
- Filling out these tiny boxes
is fucking agony.

01:09.413 --> 01:11.310
What kind of sadist
created these forms?

01:11.379 --> 01:14.586
- Somebody with
a short last name.

01:15.793 --> 01:17.827
- Agh.

01:17.896 --> 01:19.724
[door thuds shut]

01:31.862 --> 01:34.793
[somber music]

01:34.862 --> 01:41.620
♪ ♪

01:41.689 --> 01:44.586
- What are you gonna do to me?

01:44.655 --> 01:45.689
[gunshot]

01:53.689 --> 01:55.724
- You fucking idiot.

01:57.000 --> 01:58.517
Cooper and I came home
from the store,

01:58.586 --> 02:01.448
front door was wide open,

02:01.517 --> 02:04.137
walked in and he was dead
in the living room.

02:04.206 --> 02:06.379
It's about
pretty much it.

02:06.448 --> 02:09.620
- Didn't hear anything?
See anything?

02:09.689 --> 02:11.931
- Nope.

02:13.620 --> 02:16.275
- This didn't surprise you,
did it?

02:17.724 --> 02:19.655
- Did it surprise you?

02:19.724 --> 02:25.034
♪ ♪

02:25.103 --> 02:27.344
- Didn't surprise me at all.

02:31.241 --> 02:33.241
[gunshot]

02:34.793 --> 02:36.655
[boom]

02:36.724 --> 02:38.206
[tense music]

02:38.275 --> 02:40.655
[boom]

02:40.724 --> 02:44.655
[men shouting]

02:44.724 --> 02:47.517
[gunfire]

02:50.655 --> 02:52.689
[boom]

02:53.379 --> 02:55.103
- Motherfuckers!

02:55.172 --> 02:57.000
- Oh, shit.

02:57.068 --> 02:58.793
- Let's go, let's go, let's go.

02:58.862 --> 03:04.275
♪ ♪

03:07.517 --> 03:09.931
- Give me a hand!

03:11.517 --> 03:14.034
[heavy breathing]
Three, two, one.

03:14.103 --> 03:15.724
[grunting]

03:20.379 --> 03:22.655
- How is he?
Can you hear me, soldier?

03:22.724 --> 03:24.379
- Incoming!

03:24.448 --> 03:28.586
♪ ♪

03:28.655 --> 03:30.758
- Jesus.

03:30.827 --> 03:34.000
We gotta get him to the cash!
- Cash is toast!

03:34.068 --> 03:37.344
O.R. took a direct hit!
Casualties there too!

03:37.413 --> 03:40.310
- Where do we take him?
- D-FAC!

03:40.379 --> 03:43.034
- Three, two, one.
Lift!

03:43.103 --> 03:45.620
♪ ♪

03:45.689 --> 03:48.310
- Three, two, one.
Lift!

03:50.965 --> 03:53.068
- All right, listen up!

03:53.137 --> 03:55.620
We're gonna triage
priority levels!

03:55.689 --> 03:58.448
You know the drill.
Red is immediate attention.

03:58.517 --> 04:01.896
Yellow is anything that can
wait six hours to live.

04:01.965 --> 04:04.344
Green is walking wounded.

04:04.413 --> 04:06.137
Anything that's not red...

04:06.206 --> 04:07.413
[explosions booming]

04:07.482 --> 04:08.896
Gets field-dressed

04:08.965 --> 04:10.724
and will have to wait
to get further treatment.

04:10.793 --> 04:14.275
I want more of these cots.
Find me more and blankets.

04:14.344 --> 04:18.275
[gunfire continues]
[men shouting]

04:20.655 --> 04:21.793
I don't see my medication here.

04:21.862 --> 04:23.241
Where the fuck
are all my drugs?

04:23.310 --> 04:24.758
- Hardly anything
was salvageable.

04:24.827 --> 04:26.482
I brought all that I could.
- You're bleeding.

04:26.551 --> 04:27.862
What happened?
- I was in the O.R.

04:27.931 --> 04:29.551
when it got hit.
- Are you gonna be okay?

04:29.620 --> 04:31.620
- I'll be fine--I had my back
turned to the explosion.

04:31.689 --> 04:34.758
Just need a small dressing.
- Good, 'cause I need you.

04:34.827 --> 04:37.241
- Anything you surgeons need
from my supplies,

04:37.310 --> 04:39.034
just say the word.

04:39.103 --> 04:41.241
I always say you can eat off my
floor, can operate off it too.

04:41.310 --> 04:42.758
- Good to know.
- Head trauma.

04:42.827 --> 04:44.724
Probable internal bleeding.
- CT scan survive?

04:44.793 --> 04:47.586
- A lot of equipment was lost.
- Fuck.

04:47.655 --> 04:49.862
- How's your leg?
Okay.

04:49.931 --> 04:52.344
Hold still.
Okay.

04:52.413 --> 04:54.551
[breathing hard]

04:54.620 --> 04:55.931
Where were you
when the shells hit?

04:56.000 --> 04:57.620
- Walking out to the wire
to smoke up.

04:57.689 --> 05:00.103
Never got there.
What about you?

05:00.172 --> 05:02.344
- In the lounge.
By the way,

05:02.413 --> 05:03.655
you wouldn't happen to have
another copy

05:03.724 --> 05:05.344
of that green card
application, would you?

05:05.413 --> 05:06.896
Spilled coffee on mine.

05:06.965 --> 05:08.413
- You're a terrible husband.
- Yeah.

05:08.482 --> 05:10.068
Yeah, from my dad's side.

05:10.137 --> 05:13.068
- Sergeant Alvarez, take Nurse
Ellis and go to the supply hut.

05:13.137 --> 05:15.310
Bring me back all the goddamn
morphine you can find.

05:15.379 --> 05:16.827
- Yes, ma'am!
Come on.

05:16.896 --> 05:18.103
All right.

05:18.172 --> 05:21.103
[gunfire and explosions]

05:21.172 --> 05:24.758
[overlapping yelling]

05:28.137 --> 05:31.068
[dramatic music]

05:31.137 --> 05:37.655
♪ ♪

05:41.137 --> 05:43.758
- Come on, come on, come on.

05:45.931 --> 05:48.000
- [coughing]
- Two, three.

05:54.586 --> 05:56.379
Let's go.
Let's go, let's go.

05:56.448 --> 05:58.689
One, two, three!

06:02.103 --> 06:03.931
[detonations booming]

06:10.379 --> 06:12.344
- I know that look.
Talk to me.

06:12.413 --> 06:15.275
- Every FOB's on lockdown.
No evacs until further notice.

06:15.344 --> 06:17.413
- Where the hell are we
supposed to take our wounded?

06:17.482 --> 06:20.068
[exploding]

06:20.137 --> 06:22.448
- Sir, QRF has engaged
the mortar position

06:22.517 --> 06:23.931
half a mile from
our perimeter.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.586
Hill two three bravo.
Firefight in progress.

06:26.655 --> 06:29.620
I'm also hearing FOB Resolute's
now getting hit too.

06:29.689 --> 06:32.344
- Listen up, people.
This is a coordinated attack.

06:32.413 --> 06:34.034
You know what to do, do it.

06:34.103 --> 06:35.655
If they won't let us move
patients out,

06:35.724 --> 06:37.172
then let's bring
resources in.

06:37.241 --> 06:38.896
Contact Bagram
and get us a resupply--

06:38.965 --> 06:40.413
- Already did, sir.
They said they'll add us

06:40.482 --> 06:41.931
to the list
but no promises on timing.

06:42.000 --> 06:43.551
- Shit.

06:43.620 --> 06:45.689
Call Camp Dwyer, requisition--
- Already talked to them too.

06:45.758 --> 06:47.034
They said at least 12 hours.

06:47.103 --> 06:48.413
- 12 hours?

06:48.482 --> 06:50.068
- Everyone's covering
their own asses, sir.

06:50.137 --> 06:51.655
You know how it works.

06:51.724 --> 06:52.931
- Let Major Holloway know

06:53.000 --> 06:54.793
we're gonna be on our own
for a while.

06:54.862 --> 06:56.655
- Yes, sir.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.241
- Corporal Durkin?
- Yes, sir?

07:00.310 --> 07:02.689
- Did the Starbucks get hit?
- Still standing, sir.

07:02.758 --> 07:04.827
- Two double Americanos.

07:05.689 --> 07:07.482
- Right-handed?
- Left-handed.

07:07.551 --> 07:10.103
- Well, it's a good job you're
an interpreter not a surgeon.

07:10.172 --> 07:11.758
- Yes.

07:11.827 --> 07:14.448
- We were maybe 10 yards from
the supply hut when it got hit.

07:14.517 --> 07:16.344
- I think she has
internal bleeding,

07:16.413 --> 07:18.103
but the CAT scan
and X-ray machines

07:18.172 --> 07:19.896
were destroyed in the blast.
- How the hell am I supposed to

07:19.965 --> 07:21.862
do this without imaging?
Damn it, I'm flying blind here.

07:21.931 --> 07:23.275
- They're looking for
an ultrasound in the wreckage.

07:23.344 --> 07:25.137
- Well, I'll take
any goddamn thing I can get.

07:25.206 --> 07:27.310
- Everything in that supply hut
is gone.

07:27.379 --> 07:29.172
- Jesus, this is insane.

07:29.241 --> 07:32.034
They haven't even given us
a timeline for resource supply,

07:32.103 --> 07:35.137
got patients that may have to
wait six hours for surgery,

07:35.206 --> 07:36.689
and there's no morphine,

07:36.758 --> 07:39.551
even though we happen to be
right in the middle

07:39.620 --> 07:42.689
of the fucking opium
capital of the world!

07:45.275 --> 07:47.103
- I think I know of a place
where the Major can find

07:47.172 --> 07:48.517
what she needs.

07:48.586 --> 07:50.448
- She's not talking about
collecting sap

07:50.517 --> 07:51.827
from poppy fields.

07:51.896 --> 07:53.620
She's speaking rhetorically,
she's venting.

07:53.689 --> 07:55.103
She's pointing out the irony
of the--

07:55.172 --> 07:57.000
- Yes, I understand the irony
she was pointing out.

07:57.068 --> 07:59.000
Thank you.
But what I'm saying is

07:59.068 --> 08:02.103
I know where to find morphine.
It is not far.

08:02.172 --> 08:03.241
- Talk to me.

08:03.310 --> 08:04.689
- There's been chatter
among the locals.

08:04.758 --> 08:06.034
- What kind of chatter?

08:06.103 --> 08:07.620
- They have seen stocks
of medical morphine.

08:07.689 --> 08:09.310
- How do they know
it's medical grade?

08:09.379 --> 08:12.758
- The vials have EU labels.
- That's good enough for me.

08:12.827 --> 08:15.068
Sergeant, if what
he's saying is real

08:15.137 --> 08:17.068
and it's out there,
I want it.

08:17.137 --> 08:19.206
I'm ordering you and your crew
to go find it

08:19.275 --> 08:20.517
and bring it back to me.

08:20.586 --> 08:22.275
- Ma'am, I'm happy to go,

08:22.344 --> 08:24.068
but this could all be rumors.
Don't you need me here?

08:24.137 --> 08:26.275
- Performing major combat
surgery without anesthesia

08:26.344 --> 08:28.344
hasn't been attempted
since the Civil War.

08:28.413 --> 08:30.034
I need that fucking morphine.

08:30.103 --> 08:32.724
- Ma'am, you don't need
all of us out there.

08:32.793 --> 08:34.413
At least let me stay here
and help.

08:34.482 --> 08:36.551
- Sold.
- One more thing.

08:36.620 --> 08:38.172
- What is it?

08:38.241 --> 08:40.310
- Are you gonna be particular
about how we get this done?

08:40.379 --> 08:42.310
- Not in the least.

08:42.379 --> 08:45.310
[tense music]

08:45.379 --> 08:49.689
♪ ♪

08:49.758 --> 08:51.344
- Hey, where the hell
are we going

08:51.413 --> 08:53.793
and what the fuck are we doing?
- Excellent questions.

08:53.862 --> 08:55.586
- Khalil's the man.
He knows.

08:55.655 --> 08:57.103
- Where the fuck are we going?

08:57.172 --> 08:58.620
- It's near this village
right here.

08:58.689 --> 09:00.413
It is
a morphine processing plant.

09:00.482 --> 09:01.931
- Says who?
- Says Khalil.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.586
And Holloway thinks
it's worth a look-see,

09:03.655 --> 09:05.413
so let's make it quick and get
back with the pain relief.

09:05.482 --> 09:07.344
- I'm at half-fuel, I just
put in a request to top off.

09:07.413 --> 09:09.482
- We don't have time to top
off--we're not going that far.

09:09.551 --> 09:10.827
- We're gonna go on
a wild goose chase

09:10.896 --> 09:12.517
with no flight plan
at half fuel

09:12.586 --> 09:14.793
while the Taliban fills the air
with mortar and rockets?

09:14.862 --> 09:16.344
- That's certainly one way
to look at it.

09:16.413 --> 09:17.827
- Is there another?

09:17.896 --> 09:19.206
- We've been ordered
to go on a wild goose chase

09:19.275 --> 09:21.137
with no flight plan
and half fuel

09:21.206 --> 09:23.724
while the Taliban fills the air
with mortars and rockets.

09:23.793 --> 09:25.620
- You've allayed
all my concerns.

09:25.689 --> 09:28.344
- Kay.
Let's take the fuck off.

09:29.482 --> 09:32.413
[tense music]

09:32.482 --> 09:37.862
♪ ♪

09:39.896 --> 09:41.379
[chatter]

09:41.448 --> 09:43.275
- Oh, come on, come on.
Get on with it, already.

09:43.344 --> 09:44.965
- I'm working as fast as I can,
sir.

09:45.034 --> 09:46.241
- Doing what exactly?

09:46.310 --> 09:47.793
- Trying to see the extent
of the damage.

09:47.862 --> 09:49.551
- Let me save you some time.
It's a minor wound.

09:49.620 --> 09:51.137
Just patch it up
and get me back in the game.

09:51.206 --> 09:52.758
There's too much bloody work
to be done.

09:52.827 --> 09:55.344
- Can't see what I see.
- Ahh, tell me what you see.

09:55.413 --> 09:58.137
- A subscapular penetration.
2 by 3 centimeters.

09:58.206 --> 10:00.000
- Superficial.

10:00.068 --> 10:03.000
- I'm looking right at it.
It's pretty fucking deep.

10:03.068 --> 10:04.413
Sir.

10:04.482 --> 10:06.275
- [sighs]
I haven't lost consciousness,

10:06.344 --> 10:07.862
I'm not having
any difficulty breathing,

10:07.931 --> 10:10.172
my pulse is normal.
Like I said, it's superficial.

10:10.241 --> 10:11.724
Now just patch it up
and let's go.

10:11.793 --> 10:13.586
- Wanna make sure nothing
is hiding in there.

10:13.655 --> 10:15.517
Can't believe
you don't feel this.

10:15.586 --> 10:17.655
- All right, I feel it.
I lied.

10:17.724 --> 10:19.000
Happy now?

10:19.068 --> 10:22.137
[gunfire, men shouting
continue distantly]

10:22.206 --> 10:23.827
[sighs]

10:23.896 --> 10:25.724
What do you want to be
when you grow up, Sergeant?

10:25.793 --> 10:28.103
- My dream is to go
to medical school, sir.

10:28.172 --> 10:31.241
- Well, I'll let you in
on a little secret.

10:31.310 --> 10:33.241
It's all just
rote memorization.

10:33.310 --> 10:34.862
Series of if/thens.

10:34.931 --> 10:38.034
The truth is, any idiot
can graduate medical school.

10:38.103 --> 10:39.620
- Very inspiring, sir.

10:39.689 --> 10:42.793
- You need instinct
to be a great doctor.

10:42.862 --> 10:45.068
Unfortunately, you're either
born with it or you're not.

10:45.137 --> 10:46.551
Can't be taught.

10:46.620 --> 10:49.517
- Well, then let's hope God
has smiled down upon me.

10:49.586 --> 10:50.965
[shouting and chatter]

10:51.034 --> 10:53.896
- Hurry up.
- [coughs]

10:53.965 --> 10:55.448
- [groans]

10:55.517 --> 10:57.206
Come on,
come on, come on.

10:57.275 --> 10:59.448
- Yes, sir.
- [grunts]

10:59.517 --> 11:03.137
Do you really work this slowly
in the field?

11:03.206 --> 11:04.758
Ah, aah!
[grunts]

11:04.827 --> 11:06.206
- Too tight?
- [grunts]

11:06.275 --> 11:07.448
- Oh, I'm--I'm sorry, sir.

11:07.517 --> 11:09.310
- No you're not.
[boom]

11:09.379 --> 11:12.758
Oh, shit.
All right, come on.

11:12.827 --> 11:14.206
We're needed.
Time's up.

11:14.275 --> 11:15.931
Let's go.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.068
♪ ♪

11:18.137 --> 11:21.724
All right, help me--
help me with these wounded.

11:27.241 --> 11:30.551
- Sir, QRF has successfully
engaged a mortar position.

11:30.620 --> 11:32.241
Three enemy dead.

11:32.310 --> 11:34.551
- Something tells me they had
more than one mortar position.

11:34.620 --> 11:36.137
Tell QRF
keep searching the perimeter

11:36.206 --> 11:37.413
and get me
that crater analysis.

11:37.482 --> 11:39.103
- Yes, sir.

11:39.172 --> 11:40.965
- Put together a battle damage
assessment of the base.

11:41.034 --> 11:43.000
I need to know what's still
operational and what isn't.

11:43.068 --> 11:44.103
- On it, sir.

11:44.172 --> 11:47.310
[tense music]

11:47.379 --> 11:54.137
♪ ♪

11:54.206 --> 11:57.275
- I hope you are enjoying
the sheer pleasure of being out

11:57.344 --> 11:58.793
while the Tally
are lighting up the sky.

11:58.862 --> 12:01.344
But it is now time
to grab your cocks,

12:01.413 --> 12:04.379
because I've got to make sure
they don't get a second shot!

12:08.206 --> 12:10.068
- Whoo-hoo!

12:10.137 --> 12:11.689
Whoo!

12:14.103 --> 12:16.000
[laughs]

12:21.724 --> 12:25.000
- I hate when he does this!
- What?

12:25.068 --> 12:28.034
It's like Disneyland except
you don't have to wait in line

12:28.103 --> 12:30.793
for three fucking hours!

12:30.862 --> 12:31.896
[laughs]

12:31.965 --> 12:33.965
- You don't look so good,
sir.

12:34.034 --> 12:35.793
- Save the color commentary
and hand me what I ask for.

12:35.862 --> 12:37.551
- I think you should sit down.
- I'm not the patient.

12:37.620 --> 12:39.758
Now hand me the blade.

12:42.620 --> 12:45.137
I asked for the 10-blade.
This is the 15.

12:45.206 --> 12:47.310
- You didn't call a number.
- Yes, I did.

12:47.379 --> 12:49.068
- You did not, sir.

12:50.275 --> 12:52.724
- [grunts]
Suction.

12:54.448 --> 12:56.379
Uh, you're blocking my view.

12:56.448 --> 12:58.482
- It's tight in there.
- Uh, yes, it is.

12:58.551 --> 13:01.344
So try not to obscure
everything I need to see.

13:01.413 --> 13:02.862
- You're getting close
to a tendon.

13:02.931 --> 13:05.103
- I'm well aware.
Thank you.

13:05.172 --> 13:06.655
All right.
Forceps.

13:14.689 --> 13:18.172
Gotcha, you bloody bastard.

13:19.689 --> 13:22.448
[sighs]
All right.

13:22.517 --> 13:25.482
Needle.
- You're really sweating, sir.

13:25.551 --> 13:27.793
- Needle, please.

13:28.724 --> 13:31.689
Now you medics
have a reputation, you know?

13:31.758 --> 13:33.206
- Reputation?
- Mm-hmm.

13:33.275 --> 13:36.413
You look down us doctors.
You think we're all pussies

13:36.482 --> 13:38.241
because we never venture
outside the wire.

13:38.310 --> 13:41.310
It's true, isn't it?
- No, sir, it's not.

13:41.379 --> 13:43.689
- The truth is,
I could do your job.

13:43.758 --> 13:46.068
It's just that
I'm terrified of flying.

13:46.137 --> 13:47.689
Always have been.

13:47.758 --> 13:51.310
Come from a long line
of RAF pilots, though.

13:51.379 --> 13:53.379
My father,
both my older brothers...

13:53.448 --> 13:58.344
Of course they're terrified
of blood, so you know what?

13:58.413 --> 14:00.689
Screw them.

14:02.068 --> 14:04.206
[metal clanks]
Aw...[murmurs].

14:06.241 --> 14:08.000
- Sir, your wound
has opened up.

14:08.068 --> 14:09.896
- No, no, I'll be fine.
- No, no, I think we need to

14:09.965 --> 14:11.344
go back in and see
what's going on in there--

14:11.413 --> 14:13.551
- Uh, you know if Tiger Woods
can win the U.S. Open

14:13.620 --> 14:14.931
with a broken leg,

14:15.000 --> 14:16.517
I can perform surgery
with a topical wound.

14:16.586 --> 14:18.724
- It's not a topical wound.
- It most certainly is.

14:18.793 --> 14:20.413
- Is not.
Help!

14:20.482 --> 14:23.413
[buzuq music]

14:23.482 --> 14:30.620
♪ ♪

14:35.724 --> 14:37.344
- This doesn't
exactly look like

14:37.413 --> 14:38.896
the high rent district to me.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.517
- We're in Afghanistan,
all right?

14:40.586 --> 14:42.965
I would like to see what your
Fifth Avenue would look like

14:43.034 --> 14:45.310
after two hostile invasions
and an 18-year civil war.

14:45.379 --> 14:48.137
- Probably look a lot
like my neighborhood.

14:48.206 --> 14:49.655
'Sup.

14:52.034 --> 14:54.344
I've seen some ghetto
pharmacies in my day,

14:54.413 --> 14:56.103
but this is sad.

14:56.172 --> 14:58.482
- Yeah, Khalil, this is not
the morphine we're looking for.

14:58.551 --> 15:00.310
- Of course.

15:03.206 --> 15:04.482
Salaam alaikum.

15:04.551 --> 15:06.275
[both speaking Pashto]

15:06.344 --> 15:07.862
Wait here.

15:13.172 --> 15:15.068
- Who do you think was the
first guy to figure out

15:15.137 --> 15:16.793
this stuff
would make him so happy

15:16.862 --> 15:19.413
he'd blow one his cavemen
buddies just to score more?

15:19.482 --> 15:20.793
- I don't know.

15:20.862 --> 15:22.379
I used to know this kid
from back home

15:22.448 --> 15:23.965
who used to shoot black tar
up his ass to get high.

15:24.034 --> 15:25.551
- Say what?
- Yeah.

15:25.620 --> 15:27.586
He and I used to work
the night shift at Denny's.

15:27.655 --> 15:28.827
But he was terrified
of needles,

15:28.896 --> 15:30.413
so every day before work

15:30.482 --> 15:32.275
he'd mix it with canola oil,
stick it in a baster and--

15:32.344 --> 15:33.793
- Yeah, I get the picture.

15:33.862 --> 15:35.827
So you're suggesting
we should turn this tar

15:35.896 --> 15:37.586
into morphine suppositories?

15:37.655 --> 15:39.586
- Kid ended up dying
of internal bleeding.

15:39.655 --> 15:43.000
Doubt it was the canola oil.
- All your stories make me sad.

15:44.034 --> 15:46.034
- Why are we wasting time here?

15:46.103 --> 15:47.896
- To get the location
of a refining facility

15:47.965 --> 15:49.448
all the locals
have been whispering about.

15:49.517 --> 15:51.068
And now I have it.

15:51.137 --> 15:53.517
Thank you, Khalil.
You're welcome, Khalil.

15:53.586 --> 15:55.758
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

15:55.827 --> 15:58.103
[tense music]

15:58.172 --> 15:59.965
- Tell me what you see.
- Shrapnel.

16:00.034 --> 16:02.379
Lodged between the four rib
and the scapula.

16:02.448 --> 16:04.517
- Oh, bloody hell.

16:04.586 --> 16:06.000
- Yes, it is.

16:06.068 --> 16:09.689
Must've bounced off the bone
and hid in the pocket.

16:09.758 --> 16:11.344
You shouldn't have rushed me,
sir.

16:11.413 --> 16:13.379
- All right, well, you're gonna
have to get it out of there.

16:13.448 --> 16:15.000
[sighs]

16:15.068 --> 16:16.862
- Sir, that's surgery.
I'm not trained to do this.

16:16.931 --> 16:19.103
- Stop complaining.
You want to be a doctor?

16:19.172 --> 16:21.724
Prove yourself, all right?
I'll talk you through it.

16:22.344 --> 16:24.206
- Okay, but there's a lot
of tissue in the way.

16:24.275 --> 16:26.379
- Well, you're just going to
have to trim some of it,

16:26.448 --> 16:27.827
all right?

16:27.896 --> 16:29.965
Like you've seen me do
on all the others.

16:30.034 --> 16:33.206
All right,
now just create a path

16:33.275 --> 16:35.482
and pull it out
with the forceps.

16:35.551 --> 16:38.275
- Sir, that'll be real hard
for you without pain meds.

16:38.344 --> 16:39.965
- Tell me something
that's not bloody obvious!

16:40.034 --> 16:41.689
- Well, I can ask
Major Holloway to spare some.

16:41.758 --> 16:44.482
- No, no!
Leave it for the others.

16:44.551 --> 16:46.827
- Yes, sir.

16:46.896 --> 16:50.344
- [sighs]
Oh!

16:52.758 --> 16:55.758
Oof.
All right.

16:57.379 --> 17:00.034
Guess I'm about to test
my tolerance for pain.

17:00.103 --> 17:02.517
- You're certainly
testing mine.

17:02.586 --> 17:07.068
[ominous music]

17:07.137 --> 17:08.931
- The fuck is this place?

17:09.000 --> 17:11.379
♪ ♪

17:11.448 --> 17:14.931
- About as far off the main
road as I'm comfortable with.

17:29.586 --> 17:31.137
- Who the fuck are you?

17:32.413 --> 17:34.310
- United States Army.

17:34.379 --> 17:36.586
We're medics
out of FOB Guardian.

17:36.655 --> 17:38.068
- What are you doing here?

17:38.137 --> 17:40.000
- We're looking to secure
a supply of morphine.

17:40.068 --> 17:42.379
We were sent by
our commanding officer.

17:47.896 --> 17:55.103
♪ ♪

18:00.137 --> 18:03.137
[ominous music]

18:03.206 --> 18:10.206
♪ ♪

18:13.448 --> 18:15.379
- Wait here.

18:17.482 --> 18:19.206
- Morphine production?

18:19.275 --> 18:22.000
Another scam SecCorp's
got their dicks in.

18:23.758 --> 18:25.103
Someone's gotta hold
these fucks accountable.

18:25.172 --> 18:26.655
- I'll be sure to bring it up

18:26.724 --> 18:28.758
at their next
stockholder's meeting.

18:32.103 --> 18:34.172
- [speaking foreign language]
Hans Ruegsegger.

18:34.241 --> 18:37.000
How may I assist you gentlemen?

18:38.000 --> 18:39.827
- We need
some medical morphine.

18:39.896 --> 18:42.275
As much as we can.

18:42.344 --> 18:44.000
What is this place?

18:44.068 --> 18:46.172
- You can say it's
an experiment, really.

18:46.241 --> 18:47.896
See I'm working for
a Berlin-based

18:47.965 --> 18:49.344
pharmaceutical company.

18:49.413 --> 18:51.413
- You're German?
- Swiss.

18:51.482 --> 18:53.448
Let me show you around.

18:55.137 --> 18:56.413
We've been testing
the feasibility

18:56.482 --> 18:58.758
of turning raw opium
into morphine here.

18:58.827 --> 19:00.448
Right where it is grown.

19:00.517 --> 19:04.241
Cut out all the shadowy
middlemen, corrupt bureaucrats.

19:04.310 --> 19:06.931
Turns out we've been saving
a tremendous amount of money

19:07.000 --> 19:08.137
doing it this way.

19:08.206 --> 19:10.448
So far it's been
a smashing success.

19:10.517 --> 19:12.310
- Smashing.

19:12.379 --> 19:14.172
- We're planning six more
processing plants

19:14.241 --> 19:17.517
here in the next year.
Our investors are very excited.

19:17.586 --> 19:18.931
- Anyone bother to tell
your investors

19:19.000 --> 19:21.413
there's a civil war going on?

19:21.482 --> 19:23.310
- We have arrangements.

19:25.275 --> 19:28.413
The world has never seen
a free market quite like this.

19:29.965 --> 19:32.413
- So look,
our forward operating base,

19:32.482 --> 19:34.344
the one that makes it safe
for you to do all this,

19:34.413 --> 19:36.103
is in desperate need
of some morphine,

19:36.172 --> 19:38.000
but we're a little
short on time, so--

19:39.000 --> 19:40.206
- Under normal circumstances

19:40.275 --> 19:42.344
I would be happy
to supply you, but...

19:43.551 --> 19:45.482
unfortunately,
everything I have right now

19:45.551 --> 19:47.206
has been spoken for.

19:48.000 --> 19:51.000
I'm quite sorry.
- Spoken for, huh?

19:51.068 --> 19:54.034
What would it take
to speak louder for this stuff?

19:54.103 --> 19:56.000
- If you want to cut in line,
it will cost you.

19:56.068 --> 19:57.931
But since you are
U.S. military,

19:58.000 --> 19:59.931
I'm happy to try
and work something out.

20:00.000 --> 20:03.000
The least I can do
is entertain an offer.

20:03.068 --> 20:05.206
- There's a bout a grand
in petty cash on the bird.

20:06.344 --> 20:09.275
- What will 1,000 U.S. dollars
get us?

20:15.931 --> 20:17.448
- For real?

20:17.517 --> 20:19.413
[ominous music]

20:19.482 --> 20:21.068
What kind of bullshit?

20:21.137 --> 20:23.000
No wonder my mom's medical
bills are through the roof.

20:23.068 --> 20:25.517
Big Pharma's got everybody
by the short hairs.

20:25.586 --> 20:29.793
- Look, those three vials
are not gonna cut it.

20:29.862 --> 20:32.724
It's barely enough
for a weekend in Reno.

20:32.793 --> 20:35.379
And we don't have
any more money.

20:35.448 --> 20:37.931
- But of course you do.

20:38.827 --> 20:40.241
- You know something we don't?

20:40.310 --> 20:41.793
- I know that you flew in here

20:41.862 --> 20:43.862
in a $20 million
Black Hawk helicopter

20:43.931 --> 20:46.000
bought and paid for
by the U.S. Army.

20:46.068 --> 20:48.517
The same army that supplies
every one of its bases

20:48.586 --> 20:51.862
with a healthy amount
of reconstruction money

20:53.000 --> 20:56.103
This is the coin of the realm,
gentlemen.

20:56.172 --> 20:59.137
And if you need these supplies
as desperately as you claim,

20:59.206 --> 21:00.931
then I suggest that you
get back

21:01.000 --> 21:05.275
into your overpriced chariot
and get some.

21:05.344 --> 21:07.413
Go, go, go, go.

21:07.482 --> 21:09.275
I'll wait.

21:09.344 --> 21:12.517
♪ ♪

21:12.586 --> 21:14.344
- A morphine
processing facility.

21:14.413 --> 21:16.379
- Yeah, in the middle
of nowhere, sir.

21:16.448 --> 21:18.620
- Run by a German guy?
both: Swiss.

21:18.689 --> 21:20.689
- In a linen suit.
- Perfect for the climate.

21:20.758 --> 21:22.586
Sir.

21:22.655 --> 21:24.034
- He wants money.

21:24.103 --> 21:25.655
More than the petty cash
we had on the bird.

21:25.724 --> 21:26.965
- A lot more.

21:27.034 --> 21:28.379
- How much money
are we talking about?

21:28.448 --> 21:30.137
- He didn't give us
an exact figure,

21:30.206 --> 21:33.103
but he kept talking about
reconstruction funds.

21:35.827 --> 21:37.517
- It's something
that can happen.

21:39.448 --> 21:42.482
But I need to know,
is he legit?

21:45.172 --> 21:47.275
- It seems so, sir.

21:47.344 --> 21:48.724
He, uh,

21:48.793 --> 21:51.137
he had a bunch of SecCorp guys
guarding the place,

21:51.206 --> 21:52.965
but none we recognized.
They're not from here.

21:53.034 --> 21:54.896
- SecCorp?
- Yeah.

21:54.965 --> 21:56.517
- Christ.

21:56.586 --> 21:59.551
That means this is some
fucked up version of legit.

21:59.620 --> 22:01.310
- Yeah.

22:01.931 --> 22:05.068
- Okay, let's do this deal
before it gets any shadier.

22:05.137 --> 22:07.965
We need these drugs yesterday.
- Yes, sir.

22:08.655 --> 22:10.896
- Take care of it.

22:14.206 --> 22:16.896
- Where we going?
- Just follow me.

22:22.517 --> 22:24.344
Stand over there.

22:30.103 --> 22:32.310
Turn around.

22:33.793 --> 22:36.379
[keypad beeping]

22:37.068 --> 22:38.206
Don't be idiots.

22:38.275 --> 22:40.551
The combination changes
every day.

22:43.793 --> 22:45.517
You can turn back around now.

22:51.034 --> 22:52.931
- Reconstruction funds...

22:53.000 --> 22:55.241
- Used to buy off
local politicians,

22:55.310 --> 22:56.965
grease various wheels,

22:57.034 --> 22:59.448
and pay off the families of
victims of collateral damage.

22:59.517 --> 23:01.827
It helps with their healing.
And their silence.

23:01.896 --> 23:03.379
- How much is in there?

23:03.448 --> 23:05.275
- That's classified, but
I usually have to refill it

23:05.344 --> 23:07.103
every week with cash
brought in from Bagram.

23:07.172 --> 23:09.793
- Right under
our goddamn noses.

23:10.379 --> 23:12.103
- Will $100,000 be enough?

23:12.965 --> 23:15.275
- Sure hope so.

23:15.344 --> 23:17.000
- I'll give you more
just in case.

23:17.068 --> 23:19.172
I'm only authorized to
disperse 250 grand

23:19.241 --> 23:22.103
in any 24-hour period.
So let's do that.

23:28.172 --> 23:29.724
[bag zips]

23:33.517 --> 23:36.000
- It feels kind of light
for this much cash.

23:36.068 --> 23:37.896
- Everyone says that.

23:37.965 --> 23:40.103
- You need a receipt
or anything?

23:40.172 --> 23:42.103
- This money's used for
the kinds of things

23:42.172 --> 23:43.655
they don't wanna leave
paper trails for.

23:43.724 --> 23:45.620
- Damn, girl.

23:45.689 --> 23:48.137
There's a whole other side
of you to dig into.

23:48.206 --> 23:50.103
- Mmm.
Too late.

23:50.172 --> 23:51.448
- It's never too late.

23:51.517 --> 23:53.137
- [sighs]

23:54.137 --> 23:56.034
Roback.
- Yeah?

23:56.103 --> 23:57.586
- Be careful.

23:59.620 --> 24:01.172
- Nice to know you care.

24:02.551 --> 24:03.724
- What about me?

24:03.793 --> 24:05.103
- You be careful too.

24:05.172 --> 24:06.758
Now both of you
get the fuck out of here.

24:12.241 --> 24:16.310
- Right, remember what I said--
one clean motion.

24:16.379 --> 24:18.655
- Just figuring out
my angle of attack, sir.

24:18.724 --> 24:20.206
- Angle of attack?

24:20.275 --> 24:22.103
You're not raiding
the bloody Bin Laden compound.

24:22.172 --> 24:24.413
Just get on with it.
- Yes, sir.

24:25.241 --> 24:28.413
- [screaming]

24:30.655 --> 24:32.103
- Wow.

24:32.172 --> 24:34.482
- How big?

24:34.551 --> 24:36.689
- Like a chickpea.
- What?

24:36.758 --> 24:38.275
It can't be.

24:38.344 --> 24:41.034
Well, how'd you miss that
the first go round?

24:41.103 --> 24:42.448
- I did not miss it.

24:42.517 --> 24:44.344
I was exploring for it,
and then you stopped me.

24:44.413 --> 24:46.103
- Well, explore better
next time, Sergeant.

24:46.172 --> 24:48.172
[heavy breathing]

24:48.241 --> 24:50.310
Oh, thank God,
the grownups have arrived.

24:50.379 --> 24:52.275
How's it looking back there?
- You'll live.

24:52.344 --> 24:53.724
Give me a 5/8ths needle.

24:53.793 --> 24:55.586
- Uh, what kind of closure
are you making?

24:55.655 --> 24:57.379
- Vertical mattress.
- Oh, no, no, no.

24:57.448 --> 24:59.241
I want a simple closure.
- My way will be much stronger.

24:59.310 --> 25:00.724
- No, but I don't want that.

25:00.793 --> 25:02.068
A vertical mattress
is not called for here.

25:02.137 --> 25:03.758
- It's not up for discussion.

25:03.827 --> 25:05.586
- I do simple closures all the
time--it'll be no problem.

25:05.655 --> 25:07.655
- Tough shit, I'm your surgeon,
and I'm in a hurry.

25:07.724 --> 25:09.689
- Sir, Ma'am--
- Stay out of this, Sergeant.

25:09.758 --> 25:11.379
- Look, I'm telling you

25:11.448 --> 25:12.862
there's a much higher risk
of necrosis

25:12.931 --> 25:14.379
if you do it your way.
I can show you the data.

25:14.448 --> 25:15.793
- You can't show me shit
right now.

25:15.862 --> 25:17.137
You're just worried about
being at the beach

25:17.206 --> 25:18.413
without your shirt on.

25:18.482 --> 25:19.896
- It's my bloody scar,
isn't it?

25:19.965 --> 25:21.620
- Private Kelly just took
a turn for the worse.

25:21.689 --> 25:23.344
- [sighs] I'm not having
this fucking argument.

25:23.413 --> 25:26.034
Here.
You can do it his way.

25:26.103 --> 25:28.000
- Ma'am, suture isn't really
my purview.

25:28.068 --> 25:29.068
- It is now.
- Wait, wait, wait.

25:29.137 --> 25:30.413
What's going on?

25:30.482 --> 25:32.034
- The sergeant's gonna
suture you up.

25:32.103 --> 25:33.965
So if I were you, I'd be
a lot fucking nicer to her.

25:34.034 --> 25:35.724
- Bloody hell.

25:37.586 --> 25:39.103
Oh, God.

25:39.172 --> 25:42.103
[tense music]

25:42.172 --> 25:49.206
♪ ♪

25:50.068 --> 25:52.413
- They left the door open
for us.

25:57.724 --> 26:04.827
♪ ♪

26:08.448 --> 26:11.827
You've gotta be
fucking kidding me.

26:18.448 --> 26:20.379
- How the hell did they clean
this place out so fast?

26:20.448 --> 26:22.068
- German efficiency?

26:22.137 --> 26:24.758
- He was Swiss.
- Eh.

26:25.413 --> 26:27.206
- What do we tell
Colonel Austin?

26:27.275 --> 26:29.068
Collective fever dream?

26:29.137 --> 26:32.793
- The truth.
Hans got spooked.

26:32.862 --> 26:35.793
- Drug dealers move out as soon
as they smell danger's close.

26:35.862 --> 26:37.793
I had this neighbor who cleared
all his shit out

26:37.862 --> 26:39.482
as soon as he found out
one of his buyers

26:39.551 --> 26:40.827
was the police chief's son.

26:40.896 --> 26:43.206
- Smart guy.
- Not really.

26:43.275 --> 26:46.689
He just moved to the next
garage over, got busted.

26:46.758 --> 26:48.724
It's Hemet, not Medellin.

26:48.793 --> 26:50.000
- What now?

26:50.068 --> 26:53.103
[boom]
- The fuck was that?

26:53.172 --> 26:54.689
- Go.

26:56.206 --> 26:58.551
- I don't see nothin'.
- Up on the left!

26:59.862 --> 27:02.620
- That's not good.
- Shit just got real.

27:02.689 --> 27:05.172
- We're not equipped to engage.
- Got no choice, amigo.

27:05.241 --> 27:07.206
That morphine's out there,
and it's our job to find it

27:07.275 --> 27:08.448
and get it back.

27:08.517 --> 27:10.655
- Let's fuckin' do this.
- Okay.

27:15.827 --> 27:19.827
[yelling arguments]

27:19.896 --> 27:21.689
- Shut the fuck up!

27:21.758 --> 27:23.586
[yelling arguments]

27:23.655 --> 27:25.827
- Khalil, who are those guys?
- Taliban.

27:25.896 --> 27:28.068
- You sure?
- Yes.

27:28.137 --> 27:29.965
They're Haqqani network.

27:30.034 --> 27:34.103
[overlapping shouting]

27:34.172 --> 27:36.034
- Talk about sleeping
with the enemy.

27:36.103 --> 27:37.655
- Swiss motherfucker.

27:37.724 --> 27:39.827
- Shut the fuck up!

27:45.482 --> 27:48.551
[gunshots and screaming]

27:59.241 --> 28:01.551
- God damn.

28:01.620 --> 28:03.827
[gunshot]
- [screams]

28:06.758 --> 28:09.551
- Well, that'll be a lovely
story to tell our kids one day.

28:09.620 --> 28:11.896
- Let's grab that morphine
and go.

28:21.724 --> 28:24.206
- [grunting]

28:29.413 --> 28:30.620
- That's it for the morphine.

28:30.689 --> 28:32.551
- Thought we were doing
half doses.

28:32.620 --> 28:34.068
- We just finished
the last drip.

28:34.137 --> 28:35.551
- Damn it.

28:40.379 --> 28:42.034
- I have the needle
through the skin now.

28:42.103 --> 28:44.517
- All right, now pull the line
up through as we discussed.

28:46.965 --> 28:49.310
- [sighs]
Do you feel that?

28:49.379 --> 28:50.724
- My, God, yes.
[grunts]

28:50.793 --> 28:52.551
Just assume that I can feel
all of this

28:52.620 --> 28:55.896
and everybody else's pain too,
all right?

28:55.965 --> 28:57.482
Now come up through the skin

28:57.551 --> 29:00.758
on the other side
and pull it through.

29:02.586 --> 29:06.000
Are you okay?
- I'm nervous, sir.

29:06.068 --> 29:09.068
- Everyone's nervous
their first time, okay?

29:09.137 --> 29:11.068
You should have seen me
with my first patient.

29:11.137 --> 29:13.862
My sutures looked like an angry
game of knots and crosses.

29:13.931 --> 29:15.862
Thank God
he was under anesthesia.

29:18.137 --> 29:22.068
You can do this, all right?
It's just surgery.

29:22.137 --> 29:25.344
- Right.
Just surgery.

29:25.413 --> 29:27.344
- Make sure the edges
of the skin line up

29:27.413 --> 29:28.896
so that there's no gaps
and no dog ears!

29:28.965 --> 29:31.758
This is of utmost importance
to me, all right?

29:31.827 --> 29:33.793
I'll have to live with this
the rest of my life.

29:33.862 --> 29:36.000
- No pressure.

29:38.517 --> 29:40.862
- How's it looking?

29:40.931 --> 29:42.931
- Pretty good, I guess.
- You guess?

29:43.000 --> 29:44.689
- It looks great, sir.

29:44.758 --> 29:46.862
- [sighs]
All right.

29:46.931 --> 29:51.586
Now loop it around and make
the knot like we discussed.

29:51.655 --> 29:56.172
Oh, remember to keep the edges
nice and even!

29:56.241 --> 29:59.241
All right?
No lumps, no dog ears.

29:59.310 --> 30:02.000
- Nice work, Sergeant.
Halfway home.

30:03.862 --> 30:07.413
- Uh, Sergeant, if you could
just stop what you're doing.

30:07.482 --> 30:10.000
This will only take a moment.

30:11.275 --> 30:15.586
Aaaaaaaahhhhh!

30:15.655 --> 30:18.965
- Then the German accused
the Taliban of putting the IED

30:19.034 --> 30:20.275
too close to the lab.

30:20.344 --> 30:22.206
- Turns out he had a point.

30:22.275 --> 30:24.482
- The Taliban replied
that they put it there

30:24.551 --> 30:27.896
to protect the lab.
- Two sides to every story.

30:27.965 --> 30:29.724
- That is when the German
got arrogant,

30:29.793 --> 30:32.448
and uh, what is this word?
Dummkopfs.

30:32.517 --> 30:33.793
- Something
you don't call somebody

30:33.862 --> 30:35.517
when they're pointing
an AK-47 at you.

30:35.586 --> 30:37.724
- Yes,
Taliban were deeply insulted.

30:37.793 --> 30:39.689
The rest needs
no translation.

30:41.862 --> 30:43.413
- Helluva shot.

30:46.758 --> 30:48.379
- We can't leave
Americans behind.

30:48.448 --> 30:49.793
- Of course not.

30:49.862 --> 30:51.413
Gonna bring 'em back
on the bird with us.

30:51.482 --> 30:53.551
Make sure they get home
to their families.

30:53.620 --> 30:56.724
[foreboding music]

30:56.793 --> 31:03.724
♪ ♪

31:04.655 --> 31:06.896
- How much morphine are we
supposed to take back with us?

31:06.965 --> 31:10.000
- As much as we can carry.
- Roger that.

31:22.482 --> 31:24.482
Son of a bitch.
- What?

31:24.551 --> 31:28.137
- That's Sasquatch's SUV.
Taliban painted it white.

31:28.206 --> 31:29.413
[laughs]

31:29.482 --> 31:30.931
- SecCorp to the ANA
to the Taliban.

31:31.000 --> 31:33.413
- And I'm gonna drive it back
to SecCorp.

31:33.482 --> 31:35.034
- Are you out of your mind?

31:35.103 --> 31:37.448
- We've been telling Sasquatch
we have what he wants.

31:37.517 --> 31:38.827
Well, now we have
what he wants.

31:38.896 --> 31:40.310
You take the morphine
back to the bird.

31:40.379 --> 31:41.724
I'm driving this back.

31:41.793 --> 31:43.068
- There's too many bad guys
out here, amigo.

31:43.137 --> 31:44.275
- I don't care.
I'm driving it.

31:44.344 --> 31:46.448
- No you're fucking not.

31:46.517 --> 31:47.896
This will still be here.

31:47.965 --> 31:49.586
We take the keys
and then we come back for it.

31:49.655 --> 31:51.310
- I don't wanna chance it.

31:51.379 --> 31:53.517
I'm driving this back.
Give me the key.

31:56.793 --> 31:58.689
- See any survivors out here?

32:02.517 --> 32:03.758
- What are you getting at?

32:03.827 --> 32:05.241
- As far as
everybody's concerned

32:05.310 --> 32:07.275
we paid for the morphine.

32:07.344 --> 32:10.137
- Nobody's asking for receipts.

32:10.206 --> 32:12.517
- We take the cash.

32:12.586 --> 32:14.517
- We'd be damn fools
if we didn't.

32:14.586 --> 32:16.068
- Now let's fucking bring back

32:16.137 --> 32:18.103
what we were sent out here
to fucking bring back.

32:21.172 --> 32:23.586
- Dust off 31,
this is Delta Sierra,

32:23.655 --> 32:26.310
we're ready for extract.
Over.

32:26.379 --> 32:28.620
[helicopter blades spinning]

32:28.689 --> 32:31.724
- Roger that, Delta Sierra.
On the way.

32:43.000 --> 32:45.931
- First thing you're gonna do
with your cut?

32:46.000 --> 32:47.827
- Buy a Bentley.

32:47.896 --> 32:51.103
Or pay my mom's medical bills.
How 'bout you?

32:51.172 --> 32:53.655
- Gonna get my family
the hell out of Hemet.

32:54.448 --> 32:56.068
- Sons of bitches.

32:56.137 --> 32:58.275
They think that they can get a
free shot at us on the return?

32:58.344 --> 33:00.931
- Look out!
- Suck on this!

33:05.103 --> 33:08.034
[dramatic music]

33:08.103 --> 33:15.103
♪ ♪

33:16.517 --> 33:17.896
- What the fuck?

33:17.965 --> 33:19.758
- I thought you were going
for the cash!

33:19.827 --> 33:21.310
- It was closer to you!
- I'm right-handed.

33:21.379 --> 33:22.689
It was closer to you!

33:22.758 --> 33:24.551
- That doesn't make
any fucking sense.

33:24.620 --> 33:26.310
Where the fuck were you?

33:26.379 --> 33:27.655
- One of the bags fell out.

33:27.724 --> 33:29.103
We need to go back
and pick it up.

33:29.172 --> 33:31.931
- We don't have enough fuel
to circle back.

33:32.000 --> 33:35.551
Besides, that RPG says it's
Taliban country down there.

33:35.620 --> 33:37.620
That shit is gone, man!

33:37.689 --> 33:39.517
- Fuck!
- Fuck.

33:50.413 --> 33:51.965
[chatter]

33:52.034 --> 33:53.551
- Don't worry about it.

33:53.620 --> 33:55.724
Everyone makes a few dog ears
on their first try.

33:55.793 --> 33:57.931
- What?
- Kidding.

33:58.000 --> 33:59.551
It's perfect.

33:59.620 --> 34:02.586
Don't worry, you'll still
look good in your Speedo.

34:04.517 --> 34:06.724
- Well, fortunately for you,

34:06.793 --> 34:08.965
you were born
with bloody good instincts.

34:09.034 --> 34:10.137
- Thank you, sir.

34:10.206 --> 34:12.034
- Stick with me, Sergeant.

34:12.103 --> 34:13.655
I'll prepare you to be
a damn good doctor

34:13.724 --> 34:15.517
without all of that
mindless memorization.

34:15.586 --> 34:17.517
- I would like that, sir.

34:17.586 --> 34:20.482
[heroic music]

34:20.551 --> 34:27.793
♪ ♪

34:35.275 --> 34:37.896
- No questions asked?

34:39.586 --> 34:41.965
- No questions asked.

34:46.482 --> 34:49.689
[low chatter]

34:55.068 --> 34:57.241
- Thanks for not just
leaving them out there.

34:57.310 --> 34:59.448
- We don't roll like that.

35:01.275 --> 35:03.275
- What do you tell the family
of a contractor killed

35:03.344 --> 35:04.896
thousands of miles from home?

35:04.965 --> 35:06.862
- We're sorry,
but your son died

35:06.931 --> 35:09.068
protecting a German
opioid corporation

35:09.137 --> 35:11.068
who split profits
with the Taliban?

35:12.034 --> 35:14.655
- You tell 'em they'll be well
taken care of financially.

35:14.724 --> 35:17.586
- I hope they'll think
it was all worth it.

35:19.551 --> 35:21.758
- They know what
they signed up for.

35:22.551 --> 35:25.965
- Well, it's not exactly Medal
of Honor material, is it?

35:37.413 --> 35:40.793
- I just keep playing it
over and over in my head.

35:41.965 --> 35:45.689
This must be what it's like
to lose the Super Bowl.

35:45.758 --> 35:48.724
- At least those losers
get a cut of the TV money.

35:50.517 --> 35:52.482
- That bag was closer to you.

35:52.551 --> 35:54.655
I'm sure of it.

35:54.724 --> 35:56.344
- You misremember.

35:56.413 --> 35:58.724
The mind plays tricks.

35:58.793 --> 36:01.172
- All you had to do
was grab it.

36:02.103 --> 36:03.965
I was going for the morphine.
- Look.

36:04.034 --> 36:05.724
Do me a favor.
Stop reliving it.

36:05.793 --> 36:07.310
You're not doing anybody
any good.

36:10.206 --> 36:12.551
- I need a receipt
for that cash.

36:12.620 --> 36:14.103
- What?

36:18.931 --> 36:22.586
- [laughs]
Just fucking with you, guys.

36:22.655 --> 36:24.655
- Stupid.

36:26.034 --> 36:27.551
- Uh...

36:29.137 --> 36:33.103
You always have access
to those reconstruction funds?

36:34.206 --> 36:35.931
- Yeah.

36:49.586 --> 36:51.206
- [sighs]
Thanks, man.

36:51.275 --> 36:52.793
- Mm-hmm.

36:55.896 --> 36:58.896
- Look, a fresh new copy!
- Ah.

36:58.965 --> 37:00.827
- I'm not even gonna
say a thing.

37:00.896 --> 37:03.413
- [laughs]
I'll get it done, I promise.

37:03.482 --> 37:05.379
I even have my own pen.

37:05.448 --> 37:07.172
- Great.
Hmm.

37:07.241 --> 37:10.758
What is your deal?
- I get easily distracted.

37:10.827 --> 37:13.965
[sighs, murmurs]

37:16.931 --> 37:19.724
Son of a bitch.
- What?

37:22.275 --> 37:24.482
- [laughs]

37:24.551 --> 37:26.310
This is the blue fob.

37:26.379 --> 37:28.413
The blue fob that Sasquatch
has been looking for

37:28.482 --> 37:29.862
this whole time.

37:29.931 --> 37:32.724
It's a thumb drive.
- Give me that.

37:32.793 --> 37:34.931
- [laughs]

37:36.896 --> 37:39.862
We need to get
that fight back on, amigo.

37:41.517 --> 37:43.482
[laughs]

37:43.551 --> 37:47.551
[mellow jazzy music]

37:47.620 --> 37:49.206
- Yes.

37:49.275 --> 37:55.620
♪ ♪
